inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getSigningJob.

jobId.description: ID of the signing job on output.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getSigningJob.

completedAt.description: Date and time in [RFC3339 format](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339#section-5.8) that the signing job was completed.

createdAt.description: Date and time in [RFC3339 format](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339#section-5.8) that the signing job was created.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

jobInvoker.description: IAM entity that initiated the signing job.

jobOwner.description: AWS account ID of the job owner.

platformDisplayName.description: A human-readable name for the signing platform associated with the signing job.

platformId.description: Platform to which your signed code image will be distributed.

profileName.description: Name of the profile that initiated the signing operation.

profileVersion.description: Version of the signing profile used to initiate the signing job.

requestedBy.description: IAM principal that requested the signing job.

revocationRecords.description: Revocation record if the signature generated by the signing job has been revoked. Contains a timestamp and the ID of the IAM entity that revoked the signature.

signatureExpiresAt.description: The time when the signature of a signing job expires.

signedObjects.description: Name of the S3 bucket where the signed code image is saved by code signing.

sources.description: Object that contains the name of your S3 bucket or your raw code.

statusReason.description: String value that contains the status reason.
